The paper deals with the Art Gallery Problem, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses lower bounds for algorithms, which involves analyzing the complexity of the problem, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The use of guards to solve the problem suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of a minimum set of guards implies that the paper may involve combinatorial optimization, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category.
